originalText.text: Absolutely do not park here. Not only is everyone here awful at their job, there's no accountability to when they inevitably damage your car. I spent a year or so with several cars downstairs at this location, and each and every car had THOUSANDS of dollars worth of damage without any repercussions. It's difficult, at best, to reach management. If you do, they're so clueless it's better off not communicating with them in the first place. It's not worth the cost to allow these folks to touch your cars. It's so, so frustrating that these people are allowed to conduct business the way that they do.

originalText.text: Don't pick this parking place at all. Bad customer service I have ever seen. They will overcharge you and don't want to explain the details for the charge. If you call them, they just don't want to talk and say they are busy. Very disappointed experience.

originalText.text: Tight spots, rude attendants, and overpriced.  This is the worst parking garage I’ve visited so far.  They yelled at my friend for bringing a very calm dog.  She couldn’t even get close to the station to get her ticket scanned and pay for parking.  What kind of messed-up logic is that….
